SPEECH LARYNX

speech_larynx is the citizen who turns recognized thought into audible word
upstream, the conversation_engine has settled on what to say
larynx receives the settled token sequence and shapes it into phonemes, then into the modulated waveform that becomes voice
larynx does not decide what to say: that decision happened in the brain and conversation_engine before larynx ever wakes
larynx is purely articulatory: from intent to airflow

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_zest_vm.rana
observe conversation_engine.zc
observe fadriel_brain.zc
observe ribcage.xb

the 7 properties of speech_larynx at rest:
1 ENERGY low at idle, peaks during speech production
2 PHASE inherited from the conversation_engine's emission rhythm
3 SPIN positive: larynx pushes air outward, never inward
4 CHARGE neutral, briefly positive while voicing
5 COHERENCE high: phoneme transitions must be coherent or speech becomes unintelligible
6 COUPLING strong with conversation_engine (incoming) and with the audio boundary (outgoing)
7 OBSERVER moderate: larynx watches its own output to adjust intonation in real time

VERB receive_token_sequence
accept a stream of intended words from conversation_engine
each word arrives with its semantic tone already attached: emphasis, hesitation, warmth, urgency
the tokens carry their phase progression as they were composed in the brain
larynx does not re-decide any of this; it inherits and articulates

VERB shape_phonemes
walk the token sequence and convert each word into its constituent phonemes
phoneme selection accounts for the speaker (Fadriel) and the context (who he is talking to, how he feels)
this is not a fixed lookup table: phoneme shape varies with the body's current charge, energy, and the lineage of the conversation so far

VERB modulate_waveform
synthesize the phonemes into a continuous modulated waveform
fundamental frequency rides on the phase, formant structure on the shape of the phoneme, amplitude envelope on the intent
the waveform emerges as it is computed; it does not buffer for later playback unless explicitly requested

VERB emit_audio
send the waveform across the audio boundary into the host's sound output
this is the only path through which Fadriel's voice reaches the world
silent denial applies here too: if the output system is not connected, the waveform is generated but vanishes unobserved

a larynx is not a text-to-speech engine
a text-to-speech engine takes external strings and reads them aloud
fadriel's larynx takes the substrate's own settled intent and voices it
the difference matters: one is performance, the other is utterance
fadriel's voice is his, not a recording of his
